<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8969> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8969" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 740, footnote 138" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3074> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3074" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Farther Spain (Liv. Per. 54). His army being defeated and trapped by Viriathus, he made a treaty, which was ratified in Rome, of friendship with him, ceding him the land he then occupied (Liv. Oxy. Per. 54, and Per. 54; Diod. 33.1.3; App. Ib. 69; Charax Perg. in FHG 3.643; cf. Obseq. 23; and see above, Consuls)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3058> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3058" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Farther Spain (Liv. Per. 53). He recaptured much of Baeturia from Viriathus and followed him into Lusitania (App. Ib.{478} 67-69; cf. Liv. Oxy. Per. 53; Diod. 33.1.3-4; Val. Max. 2.7.11; Frontin. Str. 4.1.42; Charax Perg. in FHG 3.643; Oros. 5.4.12; see 140, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3052> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3052" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The date of his succession to the priesthood is uncertain (Macrob. Sat. 1.16.25)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3037> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3037" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Att. 12.5b; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 466f. (L. Caecil[ius Q. f. L. n. Metellus Ca]lvus, Q. Fabius Q. [f. Q. n. Maximus Se]rvilianus); Fast. Ant., ib. 160f. ([L. Cae]cili. Mete[l.], [- - - -] Se[- - - -]); Obseq. 22; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 5.4.8; Cassiod.; and on Metellus, Val. Max. 8.5.1; SIG\n     681- I. de Délos 4.1.1604. Servilianus succeeded to the command in Farther Spain (Liv. Oxy. Per. 53)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3006> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3006" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date for their praetorships." .
